heaviest_rainfall.status: The largest amount of rain ever recorded is on 04 January 2025 when 36.8mm fell at a maximum rate of 4.6mm per hour over the 37.2 hour event.

heaviest_rainrate.status: Today, the rain fell at an intense rate peaking at 10.1mm per hour, one of the heaviest downpours recorded and ranked 10th from our records.  The precipitation lasted 11.6 hours and dumped 8.82mm in total.  A torrential downpour occurred on 02 September 2025 when the rain reached a maximum intensity of 27.0mm per hour.  This happened during a 15.0 hour storm when 21.19mm of rain fell.
